# 4. 天性の才能

Emu: Where's Tsukasa? It's been a while since Nene went back to practice...
Rui: He is a little late. As much as I'd like to go find him, it's nearly time for us to go visit the production team...
Rui: Still, it's so nice of them to allow us to see the directing and production teams at work. It's not every day that you get to do this...
Emu: Yeah! Let's watch and learn as much as we can!!
Shunmeiza Director: Ah, are you here to observe the production team?
Emu: Oh! Hi, Mr. Kato!
Rui: Yes, we're here to learn as much as we can from them. By the way... Is Tsukasa with you?
Shunmeiza Director: Hm? Tenma? I thought he rejoined you after speaking with me. If I see him, I'll let him know that you're looking for him.
Rui: Okay... Thank you very much.
Rui: Also, if no trouble... Would you mind if I asked you a question?
Shunmeiza Director: Yes, ask away.
Rui: About Reki Bakuno...
Rui: Why is he...not playing the lead?
Shunmeiza Director: ...
Rui: Of course, everyone here is a talented actor in their own right. However, Bakuno is on a completely different level...
Rui: Based on his skills and abilities, I imagine that he'd do a tremendous job as the protagonist, Kishi. The fact that he wasn't picked left me wondering...
Shunmeiza Director: Yes, I see. I'm constantly asking myself the same thing.
Rui: Huh?
Shunmeiza Director: I was originally going to have him play Kishi. But...
Shunmeiza Director: He didn't want to.
Shunmeiza Director: He was absolutely against it.
Rui: He...didn't want the lead part?
Reki: I-If you insist...
Nene: (Reki Bakuno... The way he plays his character... I'm having trouble looking away.)
Nene: (If I could learn to do the same... No, learning even just a little bit about how he does this would be huge.)
Nene: (He's had his face buried in his script over in that corner for a while now. I don't wanna interrupt him...)
Nene: (But I feel like we have similar personalities... I should be doing what I can if I really want to improve my acting skills...!)
Nene: E-Excuse me...!
Reki: ...is what I believe...but...
Nene: (Huh? I-Is he ignoring me...? No... He must've not heard me.)
Nene: E-Excuse me...!!
???: Bakunooooooooo!!!
Nene & Reki: Huh?
Reki: Um... Did someone just call my...
Tsukasa: Reki Bakunooooooooo!!!
Reki: W-Wah!!!
Reki: H-Huh? Oh, you're from Wonderlands×Showtime, aren't you...?
Tsukasa: Yes, please allow me to reintroduce myself! My name is Tsukasa Tenma! Tenma, written as “soaring pegasus”!
Nene: Ugh! Will you just shut up?!
Tsukasa: Hm? Ah, Nene, you're here. Are Rui and Emu not with you?
Reki: O-Oh, umm...
Nene: They went over to visit the directing and production teams! More importantly, why'd you cut in front of me?!
Tsukasa: I cut in front of you?
Nene: I was trying to talk to Bakuno first! I wanted to ask how he's able to sound so convincing.
Reki: Huh? S-So...
Tsukasa: Oh, that means our goals are aligned! I also came over to ask him the same thing! Let us see what he has to say together!
Tsukasa: So, Bakuno! Please tell us how you do it...!!
Reki: U-Uhh... The thing is...!
Reki: B-Before I answer, I would appreciate it very much if you could both first...lower your voices...
Tsukasa & Nene: Oh...
Nene: We're really sorry. We didn't mean to get so worked up...
Tsukasa: Please forgive us!
Nene: He just asked you to lower your voice...
Reki: Haha... I'm okay with this volume...
Reki: So, umm... You're here to ask about my acting...?
Tsukasa: Yes!
Tsukasa: I'd like to learn to make my character feel more human and give my acting more depth just like you! Please, tell me how!
Reki: More human...?
Reki: I mean...
Reki: Honestly... I just go based on feeling... I don't know how else to explain it...
Nene: Huh?
Reki: An image usually forms in my head while I'm reading a script. I get a sense of who the character might be.
Reki: Then, it's just a matter of putting that into practice... Mr. Kato gives me directions, I adjust, rinse and repeat... That's all, I guess.
Tsukasa: Th-That's all?
Reki: Yes... I rehearse the same way as the others. I don't really do anything all that special...
Tsukasa: (Nothing special...? But the way he performs...)
Tsukasa: (Then...)
Tsukasa: (This must be what natural talent looks like...)
Tsukasa: (No, I need to keep asking! There may still be some clues that remain hidden!)
Tsukasa: I'm sorry, but if you don't mind me asking you a few more questions!
Reki: O-Okay... But I don't know if my answers will actually help...
Tsukasa: I'm still grasping at straws...
Reki: I-I'm sorry. I wish I could be more helpful...
Nene: Oh, no... You've done nothing wrong, Bakuno. We still have a lot to learn is all...
Nene: Thank you for taking time out of your schedule to answer our questions.
Tsukasa: Thank you very much!
Reki: N-No, it was my pleasure... I had a lot of fun talking with you two.
Tsukasa: (He's a very nice person...)
Tsukasa: (But... I came out of that conversation empty-handed.)
Tsukasa: (I only have three lines... I can't what my character's feeling... If I plan on having as much presence as Bakuno, then...)
Tsukasa: (Forget it! If I didn't get my answer this time, that means I just have to keep looking!)
Tsukasa: (I'm going to do everything in my power to accomplish this task!!)
